#. <section class="sutta" id="mn36"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn36:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 36"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn36:0.2"
msgid "Mahāsaccakasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Discourse With Saccaka"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn36:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ sunivattho hoti "
"pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pavisitukāmo."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time in the morning the Buddha, being properly dressed, took his "
"bowl and robe, wishing to enter Vesālī for alms."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno "
"yena mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Then as Saccaka, the son of Jain parents, was going for a walk he approached "
"the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "mn36:3.2"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā ānando saccakaṃ nigaṇṭhaputtaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda saw him coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "mn36:3.3"
msgid "Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn36:3.4"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ, bhante, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto āgacchati bhassappavādako paṇḍitavādo "
"sādhusammato bahujanassa."
msgstr ""
"“Saccaka, the son of Jain parents, is coming. He’s a debater and clever "
"speaker regarded as holy by many people."

msgctxt "mn36:3.5"
msgid ""
"Eso kho, bhante, avaṇṇakāmo buddhassa, avaṇṇakāmo dhammassa, avaṇṇakāmo "
"saṃghassa."
msgstr "He wants to discredit the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn36:3.6"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā muhuttaṃ nisīdatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "Please, sir, sit for a moment out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "mn36:3.7"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane."
msgstr "The Buddha sat on the seat spread out."

msgctxt "mn36:3.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Saccaka went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. When "
"the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and "
"said to the Buddha:"

# “development of body” is too literal. this is not body building—the opposite, if anything.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.238"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Santi, bho gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kāyabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti, "
"no cittabhāvanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, there are some ascetics and brahmins who live committed to "
"the practice of developing physical endurance, without developing the mind."

msgctxt "mn36:4.2"
msgid "Phusanti hi te, bho gotama, sārīrikaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ."
msgstr "They experience painful physical feelings."

# BB’s “in the past” is not ideal. bhutapubba always refers to specific events at a point in time (however legendary). Saying “in the past” suggests it was a general thing, which raises the question, how do they keep practicing if their heart is burst!
#. VAR: pāpuṇissati → pāpuṇissanti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn36:4.3"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bho gotama, sārīrikāya dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭhassa sato "
"ūrukkhambhopi nāma bhavissati, hadayampi nāma phalissati, uṇhampi lohitaṃ "
"mukhato uggamissati, ummādampi pāpuṇissati cittakkhepaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This happened to someone once. Their thighs became paralyzed, their heart "
"burst, hot blood gushed from their mouth, and they went mad and lost their "
"mind."

msgctxt "mn36:4.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho etaṃ, bho gotama, kāyanvayaṃ cittaṃ hoti, kāyassa vasena vattati."
msgstr "Their mind was subject to the body, and the body had power over it."

msgctxt "mn36:4.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn36:4.6"
msgid "Abhāvitattā cittassa."
msgstr "Because their mind was not developed."

msgctxt "mn36:4.7"
msgid ""
"Santi pana, bho gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā cittabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā "
"viharanti, no kāyabhāvanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who live committed to the practice of "
"developing the mind, without developing physical endurance."

msgctxt "mn36:4.8"
msgid "Phusanti hi te, bho gotama, cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ."
msgstr "They experience painful mental feelings."

msgctxt "mn36:4.9"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bho gotama, cetasikāya dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭhassa sato "
"ūrukkhambhopi nāma bhavissati, hadayampi nāma phalissati, uṇhampi lohitaṃ "
"mukhato uggamissati, ummādampi pāpuṇissati cittakkhepaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This happened to someone once. Their thighs became paralyzed, their heart "
"burst, hot blood gushed from their mouth, and they went mad and lost their "
"mind."

msgctxt "mn36:4.10"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho eso, bho gotama, cittanvayo kāyo hoti, cittassa vasena vattati."
msgstr "Their body was subject to the mind, and the mind had power over it."

msgctxt "mn36:4.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn36:4.12"
msgid "Abhāvitattā kāyassa."
msgstr "Because their physical endurance was not developed."

msgctxt "mn36:4.13"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bho gotama, evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "It occurs to me that"

msgctxt "mn36:4.14"
msgid ""
"‘addhā bhoto gotamassa sāvakā cittabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti, no "
"kāyabhāvanan’”ti."
msgstr ""
"Master Gotama’s disciples must live committed to the practice of developing "
"the mind, without developing physical endurance.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:5.1"
msgid "“Kinti pana te, aggivessana, kāyabhāvanā sutā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Aggivessana, what have you heard about the development of physical "
"endurance?”"

msgctxt "mn36:5.2"
msgid "“Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Take, for example,"

msgctxt "mn36:5.3"
msgid "nando vaccho, kiso saṅkicco, makkhali gosālo—"
msgstr "Nanda Vaccha, Kisa Saṅkicca, and Makkhali Gosāla."

msgctxt "mn36:5.4"
msgid ""
"etehi, bho gotama, acelakā muttācārā hatthāpalekhanā naehibhaddantikā "
"natiṭṭhabhaddantikā na abhihaṭaṃ na uddissakataṃ na nimantanaṃ sādiyanti, "
msgstr ""
"They go naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come "
"or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food "
"prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal. "

msgctxt "mn36:5.5"
msgid ""
"te na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhanti na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhanti na "
"eḷakamantaraṃ na daṇḍamantaraṃ na musalamantaraṃ na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ na "
"gabbhiniyā na pāyamānāya na purisantaragatāya na saṅkittīsu na yattha sā "
"upaṭṭhito hoti na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī, na macchaṃ na maṃsaṃ na "
"suraṃ na merayaṃ na thusodakaṃ pivanti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps "
"sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is "
"eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has "
"a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They "
"accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer."

msgctxt "mn36:5.6"
msgid ""
"Te ekāgārikā vā honti ekālopikā, dvāgārikā vā honti dvālopikā … pe … "
"sattāgārikā vā honti sattālopikā."
msgstr ""
"They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses "
"and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls."

msgctxt "mn36:5.7"
msgid ""
"Ekissāpi dattiyā yāpenti, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpenti … pe … sattahipi dattīhi "
"yāpenti."
msgstr ""
"They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day."

msgctxt "mn36:5.8"
msgid ""
"Ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhārenti, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhārenti … pe … sattāhikampi "
"āhāraṃ āhārenti. Iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi "
"pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyuttā viharantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, "
"even up to once a fortnight. They live committed to the practice of eating "
"food at set intervals.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:6.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana te, aggivessana, tāvatakeneva yāpentī”ti?"
msgstr "“But Aggivessana, do they get by on so little?”"

msgctxt "mn36:6.2"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama."

msgctxt "mn36:6.3"
msgid ""
"Appekadā, bho gotama, uḷārāni uḷārāni khādanīyāni khādanti, uḷārāni uḷārāni "
"bhojanāni bhuñjanti, uḷārāni uḷārāni sāyanīyāni sāyanti, uḷārāni uḷārāni "
"pānāni pivanti."
msgstr ""
"Sometimes they eat a variety of luxury foods and drink a variety of luxury "
"beverages."

msgctxt "mn36:6.4"
msgid "Te imaṃ kāyaṃ balaṃ gāhenti nāma, brūhenti nāma, medenti nāmā”ti."
msgstr "They gather their body’s strength, build it up, and get fat.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.239"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:6.5"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kho te, aggivessana, purimaṃ pahāya pacchā upacinanti, evaṃ imassa "
"kāyassa ācayāpacayo hoti."
msgstr ""
"“What they earlier gave up, they later got back. That is how there is the "
"increase and decrease of this body."

msgctxt "mn36:6.6"
msgid "Kinti pana te, aggivessana, cittabhāvanā sutā”ti?"
msgstr "But Aggivessana, what have you heard about development of the mind?”"

msgctxt "mn36:6.7"
msgid ""
"Cittabhāvanāya kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavatā puṭṭho samāno na "
"sampāyāsi."
msgstr ""
"When Saccaka was questioned by the Buddha about development of the mind, he "
"was unable to answer."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā saccakaṃ nigaṇṭhaputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "So the Buddha said to Saccaka:"

msgctxt "mn36:7.2"
msgid ""
"“yāpi kho te esā, aggivessana, purimā kāyabhāvanā bhāsitā sāpi ariyassa "
"vinaye no dhammikā kāyabhāvanā."
msgstr ""
"“The development of physical endurance that you have described is not the "
"legitimate development of physical endurance in the noble one’s training."

#. VAR: Kāyabhāvanampi → kāyabhāvanaṃ hi (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn36:7.3"
msgid ""
"Kāyabhāvanampi kho tvaṃ, aggivessana, na aññāsi, kuto pana tvaṃ "
"cittabhāvanaṃ jānissasi?"
msgstr ""
"And since you don’t even understand the development of physical endurance, "
"how can you possibly understand the development of the mind?"

msgctxt "mn36:7.4"
msgid ""
"Api ca, aggivessana, yathā abhāvitakāyo ca hoti abhāvitacitto ca, "
"bhāvitakāyo ca hoti bhāvitacitto ca. "
msgstr ""
"Still, as to how someone is undeveloped in physical endurance and mind, and "
"how someone is developed in physical endurance and mind, "

msgctxt "mn36:7.5"
msgid "Taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn36:7.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Saccaka."

msgctxt "mn36:7.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:8.1"
msgid "“Kathañca, aggivessana, abhāvitakāyo ca hoti abhāvitacitto ca?"
msgstr "“And how is someone undeveloped in physical endurance and mind?"

msgctxt "mn36:8.2"
msgid "Idha, aggivessana, assutavato puthujjanassa uppajjati sukhā vedanā."
msgstr "Take an uneducated ordinary person who has a pleasant feeling."

msgctxt "mn36:8.3"
msgid ""
"So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno sukhasārāgī ca hoti sukhasārāgitañca "
"āpajjati."
msgstr "When they experience pleasant feeling they become full of lust for it."

msgctxt "mn36:8.4"
msgid "Tassa sā sukhā vedanā nirujjhati."
msgstr "Then that pleasant feeling ceases."

msgctxt "mn36:8.5"
msgid "Sukhāya vedanāya nirodhā uppajjati dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr "And when it ceases, a painful feeling arises."

msgctxt "mn36:8.6"
msgid ""
"So dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ "
"kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"When they experience painful feeling, they sorrow and pine and lament, "
"beating their breast and falling into confusion."

msgctxt "mn36:8.7"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho esā, aggivessana, uppannāpi sukhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati abhāvitattā kāyassa, uppannāpi dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati abhāvitattā cittassa."
msgstr ""
"Because their physical endurance is undeveloped, pleasant feelings occupy "
"the mind. And because their mind is undeveloped, painful feelings occupy the "
"mind."

msgctxt "mn36:8.8"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, aggivessana, evaṃ ubhatopakkhaṃ uppannāpi sukhā vedanā cittaṃ "
"pariyādāya tiṭṭhati abhāvitattā kāyassa, uppannāpi dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ "
"pariyādāya tiṭṭhati abhāvitattā cittassa, evaṃ kho, aggivessana, "
"abhāvitakāyo ca hoti abhāvitacitto ca."
msgstr ""
"Someone whose mind is occupied by both pleasant and painful feelings like "
"this is undeveloped in physical endurance and in mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.240"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca, aggivessana, bhāvitakāyo ca hoti bhāvitacitto ca?"
msgstr "And how is someone developed in physical endurance and mind?"

msgctxt "mn36:9.2"
msgid "Idha, aggivessana, sutavato ariyasāvakassa uppajjati sukhā vedanā."
msgstr "Take an educated noble disciple who has a pleasant feeling."

msgctxt "mn36:9.3"
msgid ""
"So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na sukhasārāgī ca hoti, na "
"sukhasārāgitañca āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"When they experience pleasant feeling they don’t become full of lust for it."

msgctxt "mn36:9.4"
msgid "Tassa sā sukhā vedanā nirujjhati."
msgstr "Then that pleasant feeling ceases."

msgctxt "mn36:9.5"
msgid "Sukhāya vedanāya nirodhā uppajjati dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr "And when it ceases, painful feeling arises."

msgctxt "mn36:9.6"
msgid ""
"So dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na socati na kilamati na paridevati na "
"urattāḷiṃ kandati na sammohaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"When they experience painful feelings they don’t sorrow or pine or lament, "
"beating their breast and falling into confusion."

msgctxt "mn36:9.7"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho esā, aggivessana, uppannāpi sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati bhāvitattā kāyassa, uppannāpi dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati bhāvitattā cittassa."
msgstr ""
"Because their physical endurance is developed, pleasant feelings don’t "
"occupy the mind. And because their mind is developed, painful feelings don’t "
"occupy the mind."

msgctxt "mn36:9.8"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, aggivessana, evaṃ ubhatopakkhaṃ uppannāpi sukhā vedanā cittaṃ "
"na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati bhāvitattā kāyassa, uppannāpi dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na "
"pariyādāya tiṭṭhati bhāvitattā cittassa. Evaṃ kho, aggivessana, bhāvitakāyo "
"ca hoti bhāvitacitto cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Someone whose mind is not occupied by both pleasant and painful feelings "
"like this is developed in physical endurance and in mind.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:10.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ bhoto gotamassa."
msgstr "“I am quite confident that Master Gotama"

msgctxt "mn36:10.2"
msgid "Bhavañhi gotamo bhāvitakāyo ca hoti bhāvitacitto cā”ti."
msgstr "is developed in physical endurance and in mind.”"

msgctxt "mn36:10.3"
msgid "“Addhā kho te ayaṃ, aggivessana, āsajja upanīya vācā bhāsitā, "
msgstr "“Your words are clearly invasive and intrusive, Aggivessana. "

msgctxt "mn36:10.4"
msgid "api ca te ahaṃ byākarissāmi."
msgstr "Nevertheless, I will answer you."

#. VAR: netaṃ ṭhānaṃ → netaṃ kho ṭhānaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn36:10.5"
msgid ""
"Yato kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito, taṃ vata me uppannā vā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ "
"pariyādāya ṭhassati, uppannā vā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatīti "
"netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Ever since I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went "
"forth from the lay life to homelessness, it has not been possible for any "
"pleasant or painful feeling to occupy my mind.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
#. VAR: Na hi nūna → naha nūna (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn36:11.1"
msgid ""
"“Na hi nūna bhoto gotamassa uppajjati tathārūpā sukhā vedanā yathārūpā "
"uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭheyya; na hi nūna bhoto gotamassa "
"uppajjati tathārūpā dukkhā vedanā yathārūpā uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ "
"pariyādāya tiṭṭheyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Surely you must have had feelings so pleasant or so painful that they could "
"occupy your mind?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:12.1"
msgid "“Kiñhi no siyā, aggivessana?"
msgstr "“How could I not, Aggivessana?"

msgctxt "mn36:12.2"
msgid ""
"Idha me, aggivessana, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva "
"sato etadahosi:"
msgstr ""
"Before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I "
"thought:"

msgctxt "mn36:12.3"
msgid "‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā."
msgstr ""
"‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is "
"wide open."

msgctxt "mn36:12.4"
msgid ""
"Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ "
"saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly "
"full and pure, like a polished shell."

msgctxt "mn36:12.5"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth "
"from the lay life to homelessness?’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:13.1"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, aparena samayena daharova samāno, susukāḷakeso "
"bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā, akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ "
"assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Some time later, while still black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime "
"of life—though my mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful "
"faces—I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth "
"from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "mn36:13.2"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ "
"pariyesamāno yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ "
"etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Once I had gone forth I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the "
"supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn36:13.3"
msgid ""
"‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso kālāma, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend Kālāma, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and "
"training.’"

msgctxt "mn36:13.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aggivessana, āḷāro kālāmo maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Āḷāra Kālāma replied:"

msgctxt "mn36:13.5"
msgid "‘viharatāyasmā, "
msgstr "‘Stay, venerable. "

msgctxt "mn36:13.6"
msgid ""
"tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own "
"tradition with their own insight and live having achieved it.’"

msgctxt "mn36:13.7"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ."
msgstr "I quickly memorized that teaching."

msgctxt "mn36:13.8"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena "
"lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi theravādañca, ‘jānāmi passāmī’ti ca "
"paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca."
msgstr ""
"So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with "
"knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so "
"did others."

msgctxt "mn36:13.9"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:13.10"
msgid ""
"‘na kho āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti, "
msgstr ""
"‘It is not solely by mere faith that Āḷāra Kālāma declares: “I realize this "
"teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.” "

msgctxt "mn36:13.11"
msgid "addhā āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharatī’ti."
msgstr "Surely he meditates knowing and seeing this teaching.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:13.12"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, aggivessana, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn36:13.13"
msgid ""
"‘kittāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend Kālāma, to what extent do you say you’ve realized this teaching "
"with your own insight?’"

msgctxt "mn36:13.14"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aggivessana, āḷāro kālāmo ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi."
msgstr "When I said this, he declared the dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "mn36:13.15"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:13.16"
msgid "‘na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;"
msgstr "‘It’s not just Āḷāra Kālāma who has faith,"

msgctxt "mn36:13.17"
msgid "na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi vīriyaṃ, mayhampatthi vīriyaṃ;"
msgstr "energy,"

msgctxt "mn36:13.18"
msgid "na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi sati, mayhampatthi sati;"
msgstr "mindfulness,"

msgctxt "mn36:13.19"
msgid "na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi samādhi, mayhampatthi samādhi;"
msgstr "immersion,"

msgctxt "mn36:13.20"
msgid "na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi paññā, mayhampatthi paññā;"
msgstr "and wisdom; I too have these things."

msgctxt "mn36:13.21"
msgid ""
"yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ āḷāro kālāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja "
"viharāmīti pavedeti tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Āḷāra Kālāma "
"says he has realized with his own insight?’"

msgctxt "mn36:13.22"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having "
"achieved it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:14.1"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, aggivessana, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn36:14.2"
msgid ""
"‘ettāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja pavedesī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend Kālāma, have you realized this teaching with your own insight up "
"to this point, and declare it having achieved it?’"

msgctxt "mn36:14.3"
msgid ""
"‘Ettāvatā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja pavedemī’ti."
msgstr "‘I have, reverend.’"

msgctxt "mn36:14.4"
msgid ""
"‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and "
"live having achieved it.’"

msgctxt "mn36:14.5"
msgid "‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso, "
msgstr "‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate "

msgctxt "mn36:14.6"
msgid "ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma."
msgstr "to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!"

msgctxt "mn36:14.7"
msgid ""
"Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi taṃ tvaṃ "
"dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi;"
msgstr ""
"So the teaching that I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having "
"achieved it, you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved "
"it."

msgctxt "mn36:14.8"
msgid ""
"yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi tamahaṃ "
"dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi."
msgstr ""
"The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having "
"achieved it, I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved "
"it."

msgctxt "mn36:14.9"
msgid ""
"Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi "
"tamahaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi."
msgstr ""
"So the teaching that I know, you know, and the teaching you know, I know."

msgctxt "mn36:14.10"
msgid "Iti yādiso ahaṃ tādiso tuvaṃ, yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso ahaṃ."
msgstr "I am like you and you are like me."

msgctxt "mn36:14.11"
msgid "Ehi dāni, āvuso, ubhova santā imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharāmā’ti."
msgstr "Come now, reverend! We should both lead this community together.’"

#. VAR: attano → idaṃ padaṃ bj, s1-3, pts1 potthakesu
msgctxt "mn36:14.12"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, aggivessana, āḷāro kālāmo ācariyo me samāno attano antevāsiṃ maṃ "
"samānaṃ attanā samasamaṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi."
msgstr ""
"And that is how my teacher Āḷāra Kālāma placed me, his student, on the same "
"position as him, and honored me with lofty praise."

msgctxt "mn36:14.13"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:14.14"
msgid ""
"‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya "
"na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva ākiñcaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, "
"peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as "
"rebirth in the dimension of nothingness.’"

msgctxt "mn36:14.15"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja "
"apakkamiṃ."
msgstr "Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:15.1"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ "
"pariyesamāno yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ "
"rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime "
"peace. I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn36:15.2"
msgid "‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aggivessana, udako rāmaputto maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Uddaka replied:"

msgctxt "mn36:15.4"
msgid "‘viharatāyasmā, "
msgstr "‘Stay, venerable. "

msgctxt "mn36:15.5"
msgid ""
"tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own "
"tradition with their own insight and live having achieved it.’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.6"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ."
msgstr "I quickly memorized that teaching."

msgctxt "mn36:15.7"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena "
"lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi theravādañca, ‘jānāmi passāmī’ti ca "
"paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca."
msgstr ""
"So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with "
"knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so "
"did others."

msgctxt "mn36:15.8"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:15.9"
msgid ""
"‘na kho rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi."
msgstr ""
"‘It is not solely by mere faith that Rāma declared: “I realize this teaching "
"with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”"

msgctxt "mn36:15.10"
msgid "Addhā rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ vihāsī’ti."
msgstr "Surely he meditated knowing and seeing this teaching.’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.11"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, aggivessana, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; "
"upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn36:15.12"
msgid ""
"‘kittāvatā no āvuso rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja "
"viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, to what extent did Rāma say he’d realized this teaching with his "
"own insight?’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.13"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, aggivessana, udako rāmaputto nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi."
msgstr ""
"When I said this, Uddaka, son of Rāma, declared the dimension of neither "
"perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "mn36:15.14"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:15.15"
msgid "‘na kho rāmasseva ahosi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;"
msgstr "‘It’s not just Rāma who had faith,"

msgctxt "mn36:15.16"
msgid "na kho rāmasseva ahosi vīriyaṃ, mayhampatthi vīriyaṃ;"
msgstr "energy,"

msgctxt "mn36:15.17"
msgid "na kho rāmasseva ahosi sati, mayhampatthi sati;"
msgstr "mindfulness,"

msgctxt "mn36:15.18"
msgid "na kho rāmasseva ahosi samādhi, mayhampatthi samādhi;"
msgstr "immersion,"

msgctxt "mn36:15.19"
msgid "na kho rāmasseva ahosi paññā, mayhampatthi paññā;"
msgstr "and wisdom; I too have these things."

msgctxt "mn36:15.20"
msgid ""
"yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti "
"pavedesi tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Rāma said he "
"had realized with his own insight?’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.21"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having "
"achieved it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:15.22"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, aggivessana, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; "
"upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn36:15.23"
msgid ""
"‘ettāvatā no āvuso rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja "
"pavedesī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, had Rāma realized this teaching with his own insight up to this "
"point, and declared it having achieved it?’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.24"
msgid ""
"‘Ettāvatā kho āvuso rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja "
"pavedesī’ti."
msgstr "‘He had, reverend.’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.25"
msgid ""
"‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and "
"live having achieved it.’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.26"
msgid "‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso, "
msgstr "‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate "

msgctxt "mn36:15.27"
msgid "ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma."
msgstr "to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!"

msgctxt "mn36:15.28"
msgid ""
"Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi, taṃ "
"tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi; yaṃ tvaṃ "
"dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi, taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo "
"sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi."
msgstr ""
"The teaching that Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared "
"having achieved it, you have realized with your own insight, and live having "
"achieved it. The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and "
"live having achieved it, Rāma had realized with his own insight, and "
"declared having achieved it."

msgctxt "mn36:15.29"
msgid ""
"Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ "
"jānāsi taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi."
msgstr ""
"So the teaching that Rāma directly knew, you know, and the teaching you "
"know, Rāma directly knew."

msgctxt "mn36:15.30"
msgid "Iti yādiso rāmo ahosi tādiso tuvaṃ; yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso rāmo ahosi."
msgstr "Rāma was like you and you are like Rāma."

msgctxt "mn36:15.31"
msgid "Ehi dāni, āvuso, tuvaṃ imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharā’ti."
msgstr "Come now, reverend! You should lead this community.’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.32"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, aggivessana, udako rāmaputto sabrahmacārī me samāno ācariyaṭṭhāne "
"ca maṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi."
msgstr ""
"And that is how my spiritual companion Uddaka, son of Rāma, placed me in the "
"position of a teacher, and honored me with lofty praise."

msgctxt "mn36:15.33"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:15.34"
msgid ""
"‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya "
"na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, "
"peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as "
"rebirth in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’"

msgctxt "mn36:15.35"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja "
"apakkamiṃ."
msgstr "Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:16.1"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, kiṅkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ "
"pariyesamāno magadhesu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena uruvelā senānigamo "
"tadavasariṃ."
msgstr ""
"I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime "
"peace. Traveling stage by stage in the Magadhan lands, I arrived at "
"Senanigama near Uruvelā."

msgctxt "mn36:16.2"
msgid ""
"Tatthaddasaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ bhūmibhāgaṃ, pāsādikañca vanasaṇḍaṃ, nadiñca "
"sandantiṃ setakaṃ supatitthaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ, samantā ca gocaragāmaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There I saw a delightful park, a lovely grove with a flowing river that was "
"clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby was a village to go for "
"alms."

msgctxt "mn36:16.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:16.4"
msgid ""
"‘ramaṇīyo vata bho bhūmibhāgo, pāsādiko ca vanasaṇḍo, nadī ca sandati setakā "
"supatitthā ramaṇīyā, samantā ca gocaragāmo."
msgstr ""
"‘This park is truly delightful, a lovely grove with a flowing river that’s "
"clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby there’s a village to go "
"for alms."

msgctxt "mn36:16.5"
msgid "Alaṃ vatidaṃ kulaputtassa padhānatthikassa padhānāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"This is good enough for a respectable person who wishes to put forth effort "
"in meditation.’"

msgctxt "mn36:16.6"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tattheva nisīdiṃ "
msgstr "So I sat down right there, thinking: "

msgctxt "mn36:16.7"
msgid "‘alamidaṃ padhānāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘This is good enough for meditation.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.241"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:17.1"
msgid ""
"Apissumaṃ, aggivessana, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā."
msgstr ""
"And then these three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, "
"nor learned before in the past, occurred to me."

msgctxt "mn36:17.2"
