#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.245"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:25.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:25.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti."
msgstr "‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’"

msgctxt "mn36:25.3"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse "
"uparundhiṃ."
msgstr "So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears."

msgctxt "mn36:25.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu "
"uparuddhesu adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho hoti."
msgstr "But then there was an intense burning in my body,"

msgctxt "mn36:25.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, dve balavanto purisā dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ "
"nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuyā santāpeyyuṃ samparitāpeyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"like two strong men grabbing a weaker man by the arms to burn and scorch him "
"on a pit of glowing coals."

msgctxt "mn36:25.6"
msgid ""
"evameva kho me, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu "
"uparuddhesu adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn36:25.7"
msgid ""
"Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, aggivessana, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ upaṭṭhitā sati "
"asammuṭṭhā. Sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho teneva "
"dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato."
msgstr ""
"My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established "
"and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too "
"hard with that painful striving."

msgctxt "mn36:25.8"
msgid ""
"Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "But even such painful feeling did not occupy my mind."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:26.1"
msgid "Apissu maṃ, aggivessana, devatā disvā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Then some deities saw me and said:"

msgctxt "mn36:26.2"
msgid "‘kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama is dead.’"

msgctxt "mn36:26.3"
msgid "Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Others said:"

msgctxt "mn36:26.4"
msgid "‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, api ca kālaṃ karotī’ti."
msgstr "‘He’s not dead, but he’s dying.’"

msgctxt "mn36:26.5"
msgid "Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Others said:"

#. VAR: vihāro tveva so → vihārotveveso (bj)
#. VAR: arahato evarūpo hotī’ti → vihārotveveso arahato ti
msgctxt "mn36:26.6"
msgid ""
"‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, napi kālaṃ karoti, arahaṃ samaṇo gotamo, vihāro "
"tveva so arahato evarūpo hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘He’s not dead or dying. The ascetic Gotama is a perfected one, for that is "
"how the perfected ones live.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:27.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:27.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr "‘Why don’t I practice completely cutting off food?’"

msgctxt "mn36:27.3"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, aggivessana, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "But deities came to me and said:"

msgctxt "mn36:27.4"
msgid "‘mā kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajji."
msgstr "‘Good sir, don’t practice totally cutting off food."

#. VAR: ajjhohāressāma → ajjhoharissāma (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn36:27.5"
msgid ""
"Sace kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjissasi, tassa te "
"mayaṃ dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāressāma, tāya tvaṃ yāpessasī’ti."
msgstr ""
"If you do, we’ll infuse divine nectar into your pores and you will live on "
"that.’"

msgctxt "mn36:27.6"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then I thought:"

#. VAR: ajjhohāreyyuṃ → ajjhohareyyuṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: ajajjitaṃ → ajaddhukaṃ (bj, pts1) | jaddhukaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn36:27.7"
msgid ""
"‘ahañceva kho pana sabbaso ajajjitaṃ paṭijāneyyaṃ, imā ca me devatā dibbaṃ "
"ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāreyyuṃ, tāya cāhaṃ yāpeyyaṃ, taṃ mamassa musā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If I claim to be completely fasting while these deities are infusing divine "
"nectar in my pores, that would be a lie on my part.’"

msgctxt "mn36:27.8"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tā devatā paccācikkhāmi, ‘halan’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "So I dismissed those deities, saying, ‘There’s no need.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.246"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:28.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:28.2"
msgid ""
"‘yannūnāhaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ, pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā "
"muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā "
"hareṇukayūsan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Why don’t I just take a little bit of food each time, a cup of broth made "
"from mung beans, lentils, chick peas, or green gram.’"

msgctxt "mn36:28.3"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ, pasataṃ pasataṃ, "
"yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā "
"hareṇukayūsaṃ."
msgstr "So that’s what I did,"

msgctxt "mn36:28.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato, pasataṃ pasataṃ, "
"yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā "
"hareṇukayūsaṃ, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti."
msgstr "until my body became extremely emaciated."

msgctxt "mn36:28.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me "
"aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, my limbs became like the joints of an eighty year "
"old or a corpse,"

msgctxt "mn36:28.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr "my bottom became like a camel’s hoof,"

msgctxt "mn36:28.7"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako uṇṇatāvanato hoti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr "my vertebrae stuck out like beads on a string,"

msgctxt "mn36:28.8"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me "
"phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr "and my ribs were as gaunt as the broken-down rafters on an old barn."

msgctxt "mn36:28.9"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti;"
" evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, the gleam of my eyes sank deep in their sockets, "
"like the gleam of water sunk deep down a well."

msgctxt "mn36:28.10"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti "
"sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, my scalp shriveled and withered like a green bitter-"
"gourd in the wind and sun."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:28.11"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmīti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva "
"pariggaṇhāmi, piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmīti udaracchaviṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, "
"yāvassu me, aggivessana, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, the skin of my belly stuck to my backbone, so that "
"when I tried to rub the skin of my belly I grabbed my backbone, and when I "
"tried to rub my backbone I rubbed the skin of my belly."

msgctxt "mn36:28.12"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmīti tattheva avakujjo "
"papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, when I tried to urinate or defecate I fell face "
"down right there."

msgctxt "mn36:28.13"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, imameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anumajjāmi. "
"Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, pāṇinā gattāni anumajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni "
"kāyasmā papatanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs "
"with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:29.1"
msgid ""
"Apissu maṃ, aggivessana, manussā disvā evamāhaṃsu: ‘kāḷo samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "Then some people saw me and said: ‘The ascetic Gotama is black.’"

msgctxt "mn36:29.2"
msgid ""
"Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, sāmo samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "Some said: ‘He’s not black, he’s brown.’"

msgctxt "mn36:29.3"
msgid ""
"Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, napi sāmo, maṅguracchavi "
"samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr ""
"Some said: ‘He’s neither black nor brown. The ascetic Gotama has tawny skin.’"

msgctxt "mn36:29.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvassu me, aggivessana, tāva parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto upahato hoti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"That’s how far the pure, bright complexion of my skin had been ruined by "
"taking so little food."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.247"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:30.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then I thought:"

msgctxt "mn36:30.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye kho keci atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā "
"kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayiṃsu, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"‘Whatever ascetics and brahmins have experienced painful, sharp, severe, "
"acute feelings due to overexertion—whether in the past, future, or present—"
"this is as far as it goes, no-one has done more than this."

msgctxt "mn36:30.3"
msgid ""
"Yepi hi keci anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā "
"kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayissanti, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn36:30.4"
msgid ""
"Yepi hi keci etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā "
"kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn36:30.5"
msgid ""
"Na kho panāhaṃ imāya kaṭukāya dukkarakārikāya adhigacchāmi uttari "
"manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But I have not achieved any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision "
"worthy of the noble ones by this severe, grueling work."

msgctxt "mn36:30.6"
msgid "Siyā nu kho añño maggo bodhāyā’ti?"
msgstr "Could there be another path to awakening?’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya31"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:31.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:31.2"
msgid ""
"‘abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ pitu sakkassa kammante sītāya jambucchāyāya nisinno "
"vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ "
"pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharitā."
msgstr ""
"‘I recall sitting in the cool shade of the rose-apple tree while my father "
"the Sakyan was off working. Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded "
"from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, "
"which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind "
"and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn36:31.3"
msgid "Siyā nu kho eso maggo bodhāyā’ti?"
msgstr "Could that be the path to awakening?’"

msgctxt "mn36:31.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, satānusāri viññāṇaṃ ahosi:"
msgstr "Stemming from that memory came the realization:"

# In Dhp 274 we have the phrase Eseva maggo natthañño, so eva must mean “only” here.
msgctxt "mn36:31.5"
msgid "‘eseva maggo bodhāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘<em>That</em> is the path to awakening!’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya32"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:32.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn36:32.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi, yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi "
"aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Why am I afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual "
"pleasures or unskillful qualities?’"

msgctxt "mn36:32.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then I thought:"

msgctxt "mn36:32.4"
msgid ""
"‘na kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi, yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra "
"akusalehi dhammehī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’m not afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual "
"pleasures or unskillful qualities.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya33"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:33.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then I thought:"

msgctxt "mn36:33.2"
msgid ""
"‘na kho taṃ sukaraṃ sukhaṃ adhigantuṃ evaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyena, "
"yannūnāhaṃ oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ odanakummāsan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I can’t achieve that pleasure with a body so excessively emaciated. Why don’"
"t I eat some solid food, some rice and porridge?’"

msgctxt "mn36:33.3"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ."
msgstr "So I ate some solid food."

#. VAR: pañca → pañcavaggiyā (aññasuttesu)
msgctxt "mn36:33.4"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana maṃ, aggivessana, samayena pañca bhikkhū paccupaṭṭhitā honti:"
msgstr "Now at that time the five mendicants were attending on me, thinking:"

msgctxt "mn36:33.5"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ adhigamissati, taṃ no ārocessatī’ti."
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama will tell us of any truth that he realizes.’"

msgctxt "mn36:33.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ, atha me "
"te pañca bhikkhū nibbijja pakkamiṃsu:"
msgstr "But when I ate some solid food, they left disappointed in me, saying:"

#. VAR: bāhulliko → bāhuliko (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn36:33.7"
msgid "‘bāhulliko samaṇo gotamo, padhānavibbhanto, āvatto bāhullāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has become indulgent; he has strayed from the struggle "
"and returned to indulgence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya34"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:34.1"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāretvā, balaṃ gahetvā, vivicceva "
"kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ "
"paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"After eating solid food and gathering my strength, quite secluded from "
"sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and "
"remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn36:34.2"
msgid ""
"Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya35-37"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:35-37.1"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I entered "
"and remained in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born "
"of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, "
"without placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn36:35-37.2"
msgid ""
"Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind."

msgctxt "mn36:35-37.3"
msgid ""
"Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihāsiṃ, sato ca sampajāno. Sukhañca kāyena "
"paṭisaṃvedesiṃ yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, I entered and remained in the third "
"absorption, where I meditated with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally "
"experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and "
"mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "mn36:35-37.4"
msgid ""
"Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind."

msgctxt "mn36:35-37.5"
msgid ""
"Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"With the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness "
"and sadness, I entered and remained in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "mn36:35-37.6"
msgid ""
"Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya38"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.248"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:38.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, "
"rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I "
"extended it toward recollection of past lives."

msgctxt "mn36:38.2"
msgid ""
"So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ … pe … iti "
"sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi."
msgstr "I recollected my many kinds of past lives, with features and details."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya39"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:39.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, aggivessana, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā vijjā adhigatā;"
msgstr ""
"This was the first knowledge, which I achieved in the first watch of the "
"night."

msgctxt "mn36:39.2"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute."

msgctxt "mn36:39.3"
msgid ""
"Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya40"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:40.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, "
"rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I "
"extended it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn36:40.2"
msgid ""
"So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage "
"satte pajānāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw sentient beings "
"passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in "
"a good place or a bad place. I understood how sentient beings are reborn "
"according to their deeds."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya41"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:41.1"
msgid "ayaṃ kho me, aggivessana, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā vijjā adhigatā;"
msgstr ""
"This was the second knowledge, which I achieved in the middle watch of the "
"night."

msgctxt "mn36:41.2"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute."

msgctxt "mn36:41.3"
msgid ""
"Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya42"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:42.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, "
"rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I "
"extended it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "mn36:42.2"
msgid ""
"So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘"
"ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ …"
" ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to "
"the cessation of suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn36:42.3"
msgid ""
"‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ "
"āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I truly understood: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of defilements.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya43"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:43.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccittha, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha."
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, my mind was freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "mn36:43.2"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "When it was freed, I knew it was freed."

msgctxt "mn36:43.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya44"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:44.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, aggivessana, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā vijjā adhigatā;"
msgstr ""
"This was the third knowledge, which I achieved in the last watch of the "
"night."

msgctxt "mn36:44.2"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute."

msgctxt "mn36:44.3"
msgid ""
"Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya "
"tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya45"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:45.1"
msgid ""
"Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, aggivessana, anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ desetā."
msgstr ""
"Aggivessana, I recall teaching the Dhamma to an assembly of many hundreds,"

msgctxt "mn36:45.2"
msgid "Apissu maṃ ekameko evaṃ maññati:"
msgstr "and each person thinks"

msgctxt "mn36:45.3"
msgid "‘mamevārabbha samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desetī’ti."
msgstr "that I am teaching the Dhamma especially for them."

msgctxt "mn36:45.4"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ, aggivessana, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ;"
msgstr "But it should not be seen like this."

msgctxt "mn36:45.5"
msgid "yāvadeva viññāpanatthāya tathāgato paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr "The Realized One teaches others only so that they can understand."

msgctxt "mn36:45.6"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tassāyeva kathāya pariyosāne, tasmiṃyeva "
"purimasmiṃ samādhinimitte ajjhattameva cittaṃ saṇṭhapemi sannisādemi ekodiṃ "
"karomi samādahāmi, yena sudaṃ niccakappaṃ viharāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When that talk is finished, I still, settle, unify, and immerse my mind in "
"samādhi internally, using the same meditation subject as a basis of "
"immersion that I used before, which is my usual meditation.”"

# Cp. Ss 2, yathatam yuva yuvatim, “just like a boy would say to a girl”
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.250"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:45.7"
msgid "“Okappaniyametaṃ bhoto gotamassa yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"“I’d believe that of Master Gotama, just like a perfected one, a fully "
"awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "mn36:45.8"
msgid "Abhijānāti kho pana bhavaṃ gotamo divā supitā”ti?"
msgstr "But do you ever recall sleeping during the day?”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya46"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:46.1"
msgid ""
"“Abhijānāmahaṃ, aggivessana, gimhānaṃ pacchime māse pacchābhattaṃ "
"piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññapetvā dakkhiṇena passena sato "
"sampajāno niddaṃ okkamitā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I do recall that in the last month of the summer, I have spread out my "
"outer robe folded in four and lain down in the lion’s posture—on the right "
"side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware.”"

msgctxt "mn36:46.2"
msgid "“Etaṃ kho, bho gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammohavihārasmiṃ vadantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Some ascetics and brahmins call that a deluded abiding.”"

msgctxt "mn36:46.3"
msgid "“Na kho, aggivessana, ettāvatā sammūḷho vā hoti asammūḷho vā."
msgstr "“That’s not how to define whether someone is deluded or not."

msgctxt "mn36:46.4"
msgid "Api ca, aggivessana, yathā sammūḷho ca hoti asammūḷho ca, "
msgstr "But as to how to define whether someone is deluded or not, "

msgctxt "mn36:46.5"
msgid "taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn36:46.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Saccaka."

msgctxt "mn36:46.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:47.1"
msgid ""
"“Yassa kassaci, aggivessana, ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā "
"dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā appahīnā, tamahaṃ ‘sammūḷho’ti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Whoever has not given up the defilements—corruptions that lead to future "
"lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, "
"and death—is deluded, I say."

msgctxt "mn36:47.2"
msgid "Āsavānañhi, aggivessana, appahānā sammūḷho hoti."
msgstr "For it’s not giving up the defilements that makes you deluded."

msgctxt "mn36:47.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, aggivessana, ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā "
"dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā pahīnā, tamahaṃ ‘asammūḷho’ti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"Whoever has given up the defilements—corruptions that lead to future lives "
"and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and "
"death—is not deluded, I say."

msgctxt "mn36:47.4"
msgid "Āsavānañhi, aggivessana, pahānā asammūḷho hoti."
msgstr "For it’s giving up the defilements that makes you not deluded."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:47.5"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatassa kho, aggivessana, ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā "
"dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā "
"anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has given up the defilements—corruptions that lead to "
"future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old "
"age, and death. He has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm "
"stump, obliterated them so they are unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "mn36:47.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, tālo matthakacchinno abhabbo puna virūḷhiyā;"
msgstr ""
"Just as a palm tree with its crown cut off is incapable of further growth,"

msgctxt "mn36:47.7"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, aggivessana, tathāgatassa ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā "
"sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā "
"tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā”ti."
msgstr ""
"in the same way, the Realized One has given up the defilements so they are "
"unable to arise in the future.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya48"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.251"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:48.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Saccaka said to him:"

msgctxt "mn36:48.2"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "mn36:48.3"
msgid ""
"Yāvañcidaṃ bhoto gotamassa evaṃ āsajja āsajja vuccamānassa, upanītehi "
"vacanappathehi samudācariyamānassa, chavivaṇṇo ceva pariyodāyati, mukhavaṇṇo "
"ca vippasīdati, yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"When Master Gotama is repeatedly attacked with inappropriate and intrusive "
"criticism, the complexion of his skin brightens and the color of his face "
"becomes clear, just like a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "mn36:48.4"
msgid "Abhijānāmahaṃ, bho gotama, pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ vādena vādaṃ samārabhitā."
msgstr "I recall taking on Pūraṇa Kassapa in debate."

msgctxt "mn36:48.5"
msgid ""
"Sopi mayā vādena vādaṃ samāraddho aññenaññaṃ paṭicari, bahiddhā kathaṃ "
"apanāmesi, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātvākāsi."
msgstr ""
"He dodged the issue, distracting the discussion with irrelevant points, and "
"displaying irritation, hate, and bitterness."

#. VAR: Bhoto pana → bhoto kho pana (bj)
msgctxt "mn36:48.6"
msgid ""
"Bhoto pana gotamassa evaṃ āsajja āsajja vuccamānassa, upanītehi "
"vacanappathehi samudācariyamānassa, chavivaṇṇo ceva pariyodāyati, mukhavaṇṇo "
"ca vippasīdati, yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"But when Master Gotama is repeatedly attacked with inappropriate and "
"intrusive criticism, the complexion of his skin brightens and the color of "
"his face becomes clear, just like a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "mn36:48.7"
msgid "Abhijānāmahaṃ, bho gotama, makkhaliṃ gosālaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "I recall taking on Makkhali Gosāla,"

msgctxt "mn36:48.8"
msgid "ajitaṃ kesakambalaṃ …"
msgstr "Ajita Kesakambala,"

msgctxt "mn36:48.9"
msgid "pakudhaṃ kaccāyanaṃ …"
msgstr "Pakudha Kaccāyana,"

msgctxt "mn36:48.10"
msgid "sañjayaṃ belaṭṭhaputtaṃ …"
msgstr "Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta,"

msgctxt "mn36:48.11"
msgid "nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ vādena vādaṃ samārabhitā."
msgstr "and Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta in debate."

msgctxt "mn36:48.12"
msgid ""
"Sopi mayā vādena vādaṃ samāraddho aññenaññaṃ paṭicari, bahiddhā kathaṃ "
"apanāmesi, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātvākāsi."
msgstr ""
"They all dodged the issue, distracting the discussion with irrelevant "
"points, and displaying irritation, hate, and bitterness."

msgctxt "mn36:48.13"
msgid ""
"Bhoto pana gotamassa evaṃ āsajja āsajja vuccamānassa, upanītehi "
"vacanappathehi samudācariyamānassa, chavivaṇṇo ceva pariyodāyati, mukhavaṇṇo "
"ca vippasīdati, yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"But when Master Gotama is repeatedly attacked with inappropriate and "
"intrusive criticism, the complexion of his skin brightens and the color of "
"his face becomes clear, just like a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "mn36:48.14"
msgid "Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bho gotama, gacchāma."
msgstr "Well, now, Master Gotama, I must go."

msgctxt "mn36:48.15"
msgid "Bahukiccā mayaṃ, bahukaraṇīyā”ti."
msgstr "I have many duties, and much to do.”"

msgctxt "mn36:48.16"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, aggivessana, kālaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, Aggivessana, go at your convenience.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "mn36:48.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Saccaka, the son of Jain parents, having approved and agreed with what "
"the Buddha said, got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn36:48.18"
msgid "Mahāsaccakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
